Strathcona County Transit 433A bus Stop List and Next Departures

The Strathcona County Transit 433A - School Special bus serves {count_of_stops} bus stops in the Edmonton area departing from {first_stop} and ending at {last_stop}. Scroll down to see upcoming 433A bus times at each stop and the next scheduled 433A bus times will be displayed. The full 433A bus schedule as well as real-time departures (if available) can be found in the Transit app.

The Strathcona County Transit 433A - School Special bus route map is shown above. The route map shows you an overview of all the stops served by the Strathcona County Transit 433A bus to help you plan your trip on Strathcona County Transit. Opening the app will allow you to see more detailed information about the route on a map including stop specific alerts, such as stops that have been closed or moved. You can also see the location of vehicles in real-time on the route map so you know when the 433A bus is approaching your stop.

See the detailed route map

Strathcona County Transit 433A bus Service Alerts

Open the Transit app to see more information about any active disruptions that may impact the 433A bus schedule, such as detours, moved stops, trip cancellations, major delays, or other service changes to the bus route. The app also allows you to subscribe to receive notifications for any service alert issued by Strathcona County Transit so that you can plan your trip around any active or future disruptions.

See all alerts

Strathcona County Transit 433A bus Service Frequency

The next 433A bus leaves {first_stop} at {first_stop_first_time}, and arrives at {last_stop} at {last_stop_first_time}. You can see the frequency of upcoming trips and the exact departure times by opening the Transit app.

See all departures

Strathcona County Transit 433A bus On-Time Performance

Want to know whether the Strathcona County Transit 433A bus arrives on time? Open the Transit app and view user generated on-time performance reports for the 433A bus. You can also contribute your own reports on whether your trip arrived on time, late or early. As these on-time performance stats are user reported, they may differ from official Strathcona County Transit metrics.
